'''Peter Hunter Blair''' (1912–September 1982) was an English academic and historian specializing in the [[History of Anglo-Saxon England|Anglo-Saxon period]]. In 1969 he married the children's author, [[Pauline Clarke]]. She edited his ''Anglo-Saxon Northumbria'' in 1984.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books/about/Anglo_Saxon_Northumbria.html?id=SdoWAQAAIAAJ Anglo-Saxon Northumbria] Google books</ref>

Hunter Blair was a fellow of [[Emmanuel College, Cambridge]] and Reader in the [[Department of Anglo-Saxon, Norse and Celtic, University of Cambridge]].<ref>Peter Hunter Blair, 'Whitby as a Centre of Learning in the Seventh Century', in ''Learning and Literature in Anglo-Saxon England'' (Cambridge: Cambridge University Press, 1985), pp. 3-32 (at p. 3, fn. 1).</ref> His published works include:
*{{cite book |title=Bede's Ecclesiastical History of the English Nation and Its Importance Today: Jarrow Lecture 1959 |year=1959 |publisher=Jarrow Lectures |location=}}
*{{cite book |title=An Introduction to Anglo-Saxon England, with a new introduction by [[Simon Keynes]] |year= 2003|origyear=1956 |edition=Third |publisher=[[Cambridge University Press]] |location=Cambridge |isbn=0-521-53777-0}}
*{{cite book |title=Roman Britain and Early England: 55 B.C. – A.D. 871 |series=Norton Library History of England |year=1963 |publisher=[[Thomas Nelson (publisher)|Nelson]], [[W. W. Norton & Company]] |location=Edinburgh & New York |isbn=0-351-15318-7}}
*{{cite book |title=The Coming of Pout |year=1969 |publisher=[[Little, Brown and Company]] |location=New York |isbn=}}
*{{cite book |title=The World of Bede |year=1970 |publisher=[[Harvill Secker (publisher)|Secker & Warburg]] |location=London |isbn=0-436-05010-2}}
*{{cite book |title=Northumbria in the Days of Bede |year=1976 |publisher=[[Victor Gollancz Ltd]] |location=London |isbn=0-575-01840-2}}

